<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
  <title>Installations — Mark Walhimer</title>
  <style>@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@300;400;500&display=swap');
:root{--bg:#0d0d0d;--surface:#141414;--border:#2a2a2a;--dim:#555;--text:#bbb;--bright:#f0f0f0;--accent:#c8ff00}
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;min-height:100vh}
a{color:inherit;text-decoration:none}
nav{border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:0 40px;display:flex;align-items:stretch}
.nav-name{font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);padding:22px 32px 22px 0;border-right:1px solid var(--border);margin-right:8px;white-space:nowrap}
.nav-links{display:flex;align-items:stretch}
.nav-link{font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--dim);padding:22px 20px;transition:color .15s;white-space:nowrap;display:flex;align-items:center}
.nav-link:hover{color:var(--bright)}
.nav-link.active{color:var(--bright);border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent);margin-bottom:-1px}
.nav-link.soon{color:var(--border);cursor:default;pointer-events:none}
footer{padding:20px 40px;border-top:1px solid var(--border);font-size:10px;color:var(--border);letter-spacing:.08em}
.page-header{padding:40px 40px 32px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
.page-header h2{font-size:22px;font-weight:500;color:var(--bright);margin-bottom:8px}
.page-header p{font-size:11px;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.8;max-width:600px}
.installations{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1px;background:var(--border)}
.installation{background:var(--bg);padding:40px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 300px;gap:40px;align-items:start}
.installation:hover{background:var(--surface)}
.inst-title{font-size:20px;font-weight:500;color:var(--bright);margin-bottom:8px}
.inst-status{display:inline-block;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:3px 10px;border:1px solid;margin-bottom:16px}
.status-concept{border-color:var(--dim);color:var(--dim)}
.status-prototype{border-color:#c8a000;color:#c8a000}
.status-exhibited{border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent)}
.status-permanent{border-color:#00c8a0;color:#00c8a0}
.inst-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px}
.inst-meta{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px}
.meta-item{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px}
.meta-key{font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--dim)}
.meta-val{font-size:11px;color:var(--text)}
.inst-preview{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);overflow:hidden;position:relative}
.inst-preview iframe{width:800px;height:500px;border:none;transform:scale(0.375);transform-origin:top left;pointer-events:none;display:block}
.inst-preview-label{padding:10px 14px;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--dim);border-top:1px solid var(--border)}
.view-link{display:inline-block;margin-top:16px;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);border:1px solid var(--accent);padding:6px 16px;transition:all .15s}
.view-link:hover{background:var(--accent);color:var(--bg)}</style>
</head>
<body>
<nav>
  <span class="nav-name">Mark Walhimer</span>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a class="nav-link" href="../index.html">Projects</a>
    <a class="nav-link active" href="../installations/index.html">Installations</a>
    <a class="nav-link" href="../bio/index.html">Bio / CV</a>
    <a class="nav-link" href="../exhibitions/index.html">Exhibitions</a>
    <a class="nav-link" href="../contact/index.html">Contact</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="page-header">
  <h2>Installations</h2>
  <p>Generative works developed for physical installation — projections, screens, and interactive environments. All pieces run on standard hardware (Mac Mini or Raspberry Pi) and scale to the space.</p>
</div>
<div class="installations">
<div class="installation">
  <div>
    <div class="inst-title">Bloom / Four Walls</div>
    <span class="inst-status status-concept">Concept</span>
    <div class="inst-desc">A generative bloom algorithm projected across four walls of a darkened room, accompanied by sampled Pentatonic piano notes that respond to the visual rhythm. Each session produces a unique, non-repeating bloom cycle. The piece explores organic growth patterns and the relationship between visual and sonic emergence.</div>
    <div class="inst-meta">
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Dimensions</span><span class="meta-val">Variable — scales to any room</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Equipment</span><span class="meta-val">4× projectors, Mac Mini, audio system</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Duration</span><span class="meta-val">Continuous loop, no fixed duration</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Year</span><span class="meta-val">2026</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Venues</span><span class="meta-val">—</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="inst-preview">
      <iframe src="../sketches/bloom-four-walls.html" loading="lazy" title="Bloom / Four Walls"></iframe>
      <div class="inst-preview-label">Live preview</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div><div class="installation">
  <div>
    <div class="inst-title">Traveling Landscape</div>
    <span class="inst-status status-concept">Concept</span>
    <div class="inst-desc">A generative landscape that slowly travels across a long horizontal surface — a wall, a building facade, or a public screen. The terrain is mathematically generated and never repeats, creating the sensation of continuous forward motion through an infinite terrain.</div>
    <div class="inst-meta">
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Dimensions</span><span class="meta-val">Variable — optimized for wide format (16:3 or wider)</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Equipment</span><span class="meta-val">1–4× projectors or LED panels, Mac Mini</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Duration</span><span class="meta-val">Continuous</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Year</span><span class="meta-val">2025–2026</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Venues</span><span class="meta-val">—</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="inst-preview">
      <iframe src="../sketches/traveling_landscape_page.html" loading="lazy" title="Traveling Landscape"></iframe>
      <div class="inst-preview-label">Live preview</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div><div class="installation">
  <div>
    <div class="inst-title">Technical Drawing</div>
    <span class="inst-status status-concept">Concept</span>
    <div class="inst-desc">An abstract technical drawing generator that produces architectural-style line drawings — plans, elevations, and sections — that exist nowhere and describe nothing. The work questions the authority of technical documentation and the difference between a drawing that describes a thing and a drawing that simply is a thing.</div>
    <div class="inst-meta">
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Dimensions</span><span class="meta-val">Variable — works as single screen or multi-panel</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Equipment</span><span class="meta-val">1× monitor or projector, Mac Mini or Raspberry Pi</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Duration</span><span class="meta-val">Continuous or timed sessions</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Year</span><span class="meta-val">2026</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Venues</span><span class="meta-val">—</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="inst-preview">
      <iframe src="../sketches/technical-drawing-with-elevation.html" loading="lazy" title="Technical Drawing"></iframe>
      <div class="inst-preview-label">Live preview</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div><div class="installation">
  <div>
    <div class="inst-title">Surrender Machines</div>
    <span class="inst-status status-prototype">Prototype</span>
    <div class="inst-desc">A series of generative machines that surrender — systems that begin with apparent structure and gradually dissolve into noise, static, or silence. Each machine has a different surrender mechanism: some fade, some fragment, some simply stop. The piece explores failure, letting go, and the aesthetics of dissolution.</div>
    <div class="inst-meta">
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Dimensions</span><span class="meta-val">Variable</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Equipment</span><span class="meta-val">1× screen or projector, Mac Mini</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Duration</span><span class="meta-val">Variable — each machine runs 5–20 minutes before surrendering</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Year</span><span class="meta-val">2025–2026</span></div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="meta-key">Venues</span><span class="meta-val">Miradas Tangentes, Madrid, 2026</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="inst-preview">
      <iframe src="../sketches/surrender-machines.html" loading="lazy" title="Surrender Machines"></iframe>
      <div class="inst-preview-label">Live preview</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
<footer>Mark Walhimer — Installation proposals — walhimer.github.io/projects</footer>
</body>
</html>